A resident of Lagos, Peter Okiye, has accused officials of Itire/Ikate LCDA of extorting of N20,000 for alleged wrong parking. According to Mr Okiye, he had parked by a street to take a phone call when he was accosted and fined N25,000 which was later reduced to N20,000. He added that he was forced to make a money transfer into a private Zenith bank account. “Some officials of Surulere  LCD arrested me this morning for packing by the roadside to take a phone call. “They gave me a fine of N25,000. “After a protracted argument, they reduced it to N20,000. “I was forced to transfer N20,000.00 a private Zenith Bank Account as shown in the picture above….. Is this right???”